title: Edgar Degas Little Fourteen-Year-Old Dancer Sculpture
description:
Sculpture adapted from the Edgar Degas’ The Little Fourteen-Year-Old Dancer, 1880. Featuring a young student of the Paris Opera Ballet dance school, a Belgian named Marie van Goethem. The resin figure is hand-cast and hand-finished.

  • Dimensions: 13.5 x 5.5 x 5.5 in.
  • Materials: Resin
  • Hand cast and finished.
  • Dust gently.
